Commentary Text: Chahar to Kohli, out Caught by Dhoni!! Gone! Chahar has the big wicket and he's unstoppable. He goes off on a run like Tahir. Perfect start for CSK. RCB's lynchpin is sent back early. Good length ball outside off, Kohli drives without accounting for the swing and the outside edge is found, Dhoni dives to his right and takes it safely. That is the area to bowl to Kohli in whatever format - on a good length and outside off. Kohli c Dhoni b Chahar 9(8) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: U Yadav to Dhoni, out SN Thakur Run Out!! What drama! What unbearable drama. But RCB, who almost looked like having a meltdown in the final over, have been bailed out by a direct-hit from Parthiv Patel. Very brave from Umesh initially to go for the slower off-cutter. And his execution is spot on, as it sneaks through Dhoni's attempted cut. They have to run, and Parthiv is alert to it. With the ball bouncing just in front of him, the gather couldn't have been easy, but he makes no mistake and his throw at the stumps is on target too, finding Thakur just short. SN Thakur run out (Parthiv Patel) 0(0)
